use a minimum multipole of $\\ell=70$. If\nthis challenge is overcome with improved analysis techniques or external data,\nconstraints as tight as $\\sigma(f_{\\rm NL})=4$ can be achieved through the\ncross-correlation technique. More optimistically, constraints better than\n$\\sigma(f_{\\rm NL})=2$ could be achieved if the CIB auto-spectrum is dust-free\ndown to the largest scales.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 3 Oct 2022 16:05:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-04"}
