jet) was there a potential non-thermal upper limit capable of\npowering the heating observed. However, even here the non-thermal electron\ndistribution had to be very steep (effectively mono-energetic) with a low\nenergy cut-off between 3-4 keV. The higher temperature or non-thermal sources\nin the typical quiet Sun features found in this September 2018 data are\ntherefore found to be very weak, if present at all.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 Oct 2022 12:10:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 7 Mar 2023 11:57:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-29"}
